            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think the biggest impact is on the CI where I think the cache would end up wiped each time.  It's generally pretty rare for me to want to run through large numbers of tests locally (and I suspect that applies to other people too).  So personally I'm not sure that improving the caching would be worth the effort.\n\n\"It's mostly the C compiler and linker\" is useful to know I think - it suggests that there's nothing really going wrong here.",
